  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (software-fault gap probe)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD pipeline is executed via a multi-threaded RANS solver coupled with a Lagrangian particle-tracking sub-model and a post-processing hemolysis integration script. Validation runs are reported at nominal completion; one isolated mesh-import exception was logged and dismissed as non-representative.",
